                   "message":  "ai-dispatch: GLB watcher follows in-app Open (ISSUE-258 follow-up)\n\nThe binary-owned notify watcher stayed rooted on the original `--glb`\nlaunch directory after an in-app Ctrl+O Open committed a new\n`glb_source_path`, so automatic hot-reload kept tracking the old file.\nClose that gap entirely inside the rge-editor binary:\n\n- glb_watcher_reroot_target(watched, source) -- pure, unit-tested\n  re-root decision: None when there is no source or the watcher is\n  already rooted on it; Some(source) on first-root or re-root.\n- EditorApp.watched_glb_path records the last path handed to\n  GlbWatcher::new (Ok OR Err) so a persistently-unwatchable source\n  cannot rebuild the watcher every frame.\n- EditorApp::sync_glb_watcher performs the notify side effects only; on\n  failure it drops the stale watcher (so it cannot reload the old file)\n  and warns (manual R-key still works). Called after shell.window_event,\n  so an Open re-roots the watcher the same frame.\n\nnotify and rfd remain entirely in the binary; editor-shell and\nglb_watcher.rs are untouched (single-file diff). 4 headless unit tests\ncover the re-root truth table.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
